This paper deals with the optimization of cloud computing systems, which involves distributed computing, networking, and system design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the impact of traffic load on latency, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a general redundancy strategy that achieves a good latency-cost trade-off, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The analysis of task service time distribution and the design of a general redundancy strategy involve probability theory and optimization, which can be categorized under cs.PF (Probability and Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
